n%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20generally%20a%20rare%20thing%20for%20the%20person%20you're%20interviewing%20to%20burst%20out%20laughing.%20But%20that's%20what%20happened%20to%20me%2C%20recently%2C%20on%20a%20call%20with%20Ernie%20Tedeschi%2C%20the%20director%20of%20economics%20at%20the%20Yale%20Budget%20Lab%20who%20in%20March%20wrapped%20up%20a%20three-year%20stint%20on%20the%20White%20House%20Council%20of%20Economic%20Advisers.%20The%20question%20that%20evidently%20tickled%20Tedeschi%3A%20Was%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibecession-recession-hiring-outlook-american-economic-sentiment-rising-prices-recovery-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evibecession%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20fake%3F%20The%20vibes%20around%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20as%20in%2C%20the%20way%20consumers%20and%20businesses%20say%20they%20feel%20about%20it%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibecession-when-will-the-economy-get-better-inflation-recession-trump-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20changing%20lately%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20not%20because%20the%20economy%20itself%20is%20markedly%20different%20from%20how%20it%20was%20in%20the%20recent%20past.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-november-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20down%20from%20its%20peak%2C%20but%20it's%20up%20a%20bit%20from%20where%20it%20was%20earlier%20this%20year.%20The%20labor%20market%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnovember-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20still%20strong%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20consumer%20spending%20is%20still%20solid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20relatively%20steady%20environment%2C%20people%20are%20feeling%20a%20whole%20lot%20more%20enthusiastic.%20In%20November%2C%20small-business%20sentiment%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nfib.com%2Fnews-article%2Fmonthly_report%2Findustry-report-july-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereached%20its%20highest%20level%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20June%202021%2C%20surveys%20for%20the%20National%20Federation%20of%20Independent%20Business'%20optimism%20index%20found.%20The%20number%20of%20business%20owners%20who%20said%20they%20expected%20the%20economy%20to%20improve%20and%20thought%20it's%20a%20good%20time%20to%20expand%20increased%20significantly.%20Corporate%20executives'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessroundtable.org%2Fmedia%2Fceo-economic-outlook-index%2Fceo-economic-outlook-index-q4-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpectations%20soared%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20the%20Business%20Roundtable's%20economic-outlook%20survey%20found.%20CEO%20forecasts%20for%20hiring%2C%20capital%20investment%2C%20and%20sales%20improved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumer%20sentiment%20has%20been%20on%20the%20upward%20slope%20for%20multiple%20months%2C%20surveys%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%20found%2C%20and%20it%20is%20continuing%20that%20trend%20heading%20into%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20Underneath%20the%20top-line%20number%2C%20however%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20significant%20partisan%20shift.%20Republicans'%20expectations%20around%20the%20economy%20improved%20in%20December%2C%20while%20Democrats'%20got%20worse.%20It's%20part%20of%20a%20trend%20in%20economic%20sentiment%3A%20People%20feel%20a%20lot%20better%20about%20the%20economy%20and%20their%20prospects%20when%20the%20political%20party%20they%20support%20is%20in%20charge.%20So%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%2C%20was%20Americans'%20deep%20sense%20of%20economic%20pessimism%20over%20the%20past%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20recent%20turnaround%20%E2%80%94%20just%20a%20politically%20driven%20mirage%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20embarrassing-for-me%20chuckle%2C%20Tedeschi%20responded.%20%26quot%3BThe%20short%20answer%20is%20no.%20The%20vibecession%20was%20not%20fake.%20The%20long%20answer%20is%20no%2C%20but%20%E2%80%A6%20%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Perceptions%20of%20the%20economy%20have%20to%20do%20with%20more%20than%20the%20economy%20itself.%20That%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20people%20were%20lying%20or%20that%20their%20answers%20didn't%20have%20some%20real%20economic%20motivation%2C%20but%20there's%20clearly%20more%20to%20it%20than%20the%20material%20conditions%20in%20front%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20also%20about%20their%20ideological%20leanings%20and%20how%20that%20shapes%20what%20they%20believe%20is%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerceptions%20of%20the%20economy%20are%20definitely%20deeply%20partisan%2C%26quot%3B%20Tedeschi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20say%20the%20economy%20feels%20bad%2C%20they%20can%20mean%20a%20variety%20of%20things%20%E2%80%94%20prices%20are%20too%20high%2C%20the%20news%20they%20read%20is%20negative%2C%20the%20president%20is%20old.%20Feelings%20are%20not%20facts%2C%20including%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20GDP.%20Politics%20colors%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20way%20businesses%20and%20consumers%20say%20they%20see%20the%20world%20around%20them%2C%20including%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easy%20to%20say%20the%20shift%20in%20sentiment%20is%20partisan%20flag-waving%20%E2%80%94%20now%20that%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20headed%20to%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Republicans%20are%20going%20to%20say%20everything's%20great%2C%20and%20to%20the%20Democrats%2C%20it's%20all%20terrible.%20But%20that's%20not%20really%20what's%20happening%2C%20said%20Joanne%20Hsu%2C%20the%20director%20of%20consumer%20surveys%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan.%20When%20people%20say%20their%20expectations%20are%20better%20or%20worse%2C%20it's%20not%20simply%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20election%20they're%20responding%20to%20but%20the%20policies%20they%20believe%20are%20on%20the%20horizon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20election%20of%20Trump%2C%20people%20have%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20economic%20policy%20might%20change%20over%20the%20next%20year%20and%20over%20the%20next%20four%20years.%20So%20people%20are%20expecting%20tariffs.%20They're%20expecting%20action%20on%20immigration%2C%26quot%3B%20Hsu%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20is%20that%20people%20across%20the%20population%20really%20disagree%20on%20whether%20or%20not%20these%20policy%20changes%20are%20a%20good%20thing%20or%20a%20bad%20thing%20for%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocrats%20are%20worried%20that%20Trump's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-what-to-buy-business-customers-anticipation-nervous-prices-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethreatened%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20promise%20to%20undertake%20mass-deportation%20efforts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-how-shoppers-and-small-businesses-are-stocking-up-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20make%20things%20pricier%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Republicans%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20think%20that%20these%20policies%20will%20be%20good%20for%20the%20economy%20and%20that%20Trump%20will%20help%20bring%20down%20inflation.%20Independents%2C%20Hsu%20said%2C%20are%20in%20the%20middle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20large%20extent%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20that%20small%20businesses%20and%20corporate%20executives%20feel%20sunnier%20about%20the%20future.%20The%20deregulation%20and%20tax%20cuts%20that%20are%20likely%20to%20result%20from%20a%20Trump%20presidency%20are%20music%20to%20the%20business%20community's%20ears.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20optimistic%20that%20policies%20that%20they%20like%20are%20going%20to%20get%20enacted%20over%20the%20next%20four%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Tedeschi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20don't%20love%20the%20idea%20of%20tariffs%2C%20but%20many%20are%20hopeful%20that%20there%20are%20ways%20they%20can%20get%20around%20them%20or%20that%20the%20president-elect%20isn't%20so%20serious%20about%20them.%20Or%20they%20just%20plan%20to%20pass%20along%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-trump-tariffs-inflation-goods-getting-more-expensive-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eany%20price%20increases%20to%20consumers%20anyway%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(There%20may%20be%20some%20amount%20of%20denial%20going%20on%20among%20corporate%20executives%20and%20Wall%20Street%20investors%2C%20all%20of%20whom%20seem%20to%20be%20ignoring%20some%20of%20the%20potential%20downsides%20of%20Trump's%20policy%20promises%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F12%2F18%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Ftrump-us-economy.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20instability%20he%20could%20represent%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20response%20is%20fairly%20logical%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%20think%20what's%20to%20come%20is%20good%20for%20you%2C%20you%20feel%20good%20about%20it.%20If%20you%20think%20it's%20not%2C%20the%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20there%20have%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20efforts%20to%20explain%20the%20vibecession%2C%20the%20phenomenon%20where%20the%20economy%2C%20on%20paper%2C%20looks%20pretty%20good%20but%20consumers%20say%20it's%20terrible%20(even%20though%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20they%20say%20that%20they%2C%20personally%2C%20are%20doing%20just%20fine).%20No%20one%20has%20come%20up%20with%20a%20definite%20answer%20on%20what's%20going%20on%2C%20though%20high%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20even%20as%20inflation%20has%20cooled%20%E2%80%94%20are%20likely%20a%20big%20part%20of%20the%20equation.%20But%20the%20fact%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20that%20people%20are%20channeling%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20when%20they%20evaluate%20the%20economy%2C%20which%20is%20a%20nebulous%20concept%20to%20many%20people%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20particularly%20polarized%20political%20environment%20like%20the%20one%20we're%20in%20right%20now%2C%20a%20person's%20red%20or%20blue%20stripes%20are%20inevitably%20going%20to%20influence%20their%20evaluations.%20As%20much%20as%20it%20may%20be%20policy-related%2C%20it%20is%20also%20partisan%2C%20and%20it's%20partisanship%20that's%20getting%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHector%20Sandoval%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Economic%20Analysis%20Program%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Florida%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.clas.ufl.edu%2Fpartisan-politics-and-consumer-sentiments%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleased%20a%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20early%202024%20looking%20at%20the%20impact%20of%20national%20elections%20on%20consumer%20sentiment%20and%20spending%20intentions.%20The%20research%20found%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20boost%20to%20consumer%20morale%26quot%3B%20when%20a%20person's%20affiliated%20party%20won%20a%20presidential%20election.%20It%20also%20found%20that%20over%20the%20decades%2C%20the%20swings%20had%20become%20more%20pronounced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20actually%20became%20more%20extreme%2C%26quot%3B%20Sandoval%20said.%20In%201992%2C%20when%20Bill%20Clinton%20was%20elected%2C%20there%20was%20some%20partisan%20change%2C%20but%20it's%20something%20one%20might%20%26quot%3Bnot%20really%20even%20bother%26quot%3B%20to%20note%2C%20he%20said.%20It%20happened%20in%202000%20when%20George%20W.%20Bush%20was%20elected%2C%20but%20also%20to%20a%20relatively%20benign%20degree.%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%2C%20I%20will%20say%2C%202008%2C%202016%2C%202020%2C%20especially%202016%2C%20those%20are%20where%20you%20are%20surprised%20how%20the%20gap%20is%20just%20becoming%20more%20and%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Sandoval%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichigan%20has%20been%20consistently%20asking%20its%20survey%20respondents%20about%20their%20political%20leanings%20monthly%20only%20since%202017%2C%20but%20Hsu%20said%20polarization%20had%20become%20increasingly%20evident%20in%20its%20data%20over%20the%20past%2040%20years.%20The%20gap%20was%20especially%20pronounced%20under%20the%20first%20Trump%20administration%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F5DDKT%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Consumer%20sentiment%20by%20party%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22461%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20you%20think%20the%20economy%20is%20good%2C%20bad%2C%20or%20wherever%20in%20between%2C%20we%20can%20all%20probably%20agree%20the%20way%20that%20we%20measure%20people's%20feelings%20about%20the%20economy%20is%20a%20bit%20broken.%20It's%20no%20longer%20really%20possible%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BXYZ%20economic%20data%20says%20this%2C%20so%20consumers%20will%20feel%20ABC.%26quot%3B%20It's%20not%20clear%20whether%20this%20is%20a%20temporary%20pandemic-driven%20blip%20or%20a%20permanent%20shift%20in%20how%20people%20relate%20to%20the%20economic%20forces%20around%20them.%20What%20makes%20this%20even%20more%20complicated%20is%20what%20consumers%20say%20they%20feel%20isn't%20even%20reflected%20in%20what%20they%20do.%20Throughout%20these%20past%20years%20of%20turmoil%2C%20consumers%20have%20said%20everything%20is%20terrible%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhate-spending-consumers-economic-sentiment-retail-sales-inflation-gdp-growth-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espent%20a%20bunch%20of%20money%20anyway%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20people's%20bank%20accounts%2C%20especially%20those%20in%20the%20middle-%20and%20upper-income%20brackets%2C%20are%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20spending%20as%20if%20they%20are%20much%20happier%20than%20they%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Tedeschi%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20this%20disconnect%20between%20the%20vibes%20and%20the%20data%20meant%20that%20when%20the%20vibes%20get%20bet