at%20risk%20of%20Russian%20attack.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20West%20is%20seeking%20to%20defend%20the%20cables%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20tough%20task.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENATO%20has%20a%20backup%20plan%20%E2%80%94%20to%20reroute%20some%20data%20through%20space.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20a%20vast%20network%20of%20largely%20undefended%20subsea%20cables%20has%20underpinned%20the%20internet.%20It's%20looking%20more%20and%20more%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20series%20of%20recent%20mysterious%20cases%20of%20cables%20severed%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-west-vital-undersea-cables-are-so-vulnerable-to-attack-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Baltic%20Sea%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20blamed%20by%20Western%20officials%20on%20Russian%20sabotage%2C%20has%20highlighted%20their%20exposure%20to%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Christmas%20Day%2C%20a%20Baltic%20undersea%20power%20cable%20and%20several%20telecommunications%20cables%20were%20severed%20underscoring%20the%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.nl%2Fthe-west-found-a-miles-long-piece-of-evidence-backing-its-claim-russia-is-purposely-cutting-undersea-cables%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinland%20are%20investigating%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20Russia-linked%20tanker%2C%20that%20they%20say%20may%20have%20severed%20the%20cables%20by%20dragging%20its%20anchor%20for%20dozens%20of%20miles%20across%20the%20seabed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incidents%20have%20sparked%20a%20race%20to%20safeguard%20the%20infrastructure%2C%20whose%20security%20many%20analysts%20say%20has%20been%20neglected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225251d161-3546-40aa-9949-7c96f563b6b6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlanning%20a%20HEIST%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20forefront%20is%20a%20NATO-funded%20project%3A%20the%20Hybrid%20Space%2FSubmarine%20Architecture%20Ensuring%20Information%20Security%20of%20Telecommunications%2C%20or%20HEIST.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20initial%20test%20project%20is%20due%20to%20cost%20some%20%242%20million%2C%20including%20%24400%2C000%20from%20NATO.%20It%20is%20being%20developed%20by%20academics%20alongside%20the%20satellite%20broadband%20firms%20Viasat%20and%20SpaceX.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20tests%20are%20successful%2C%20countries%20and%20companies%20would%20then%20buy%20into%20the%20network%20to%20fund%20a%20much%20wider%20rollout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f684637c-ce17-4819-bae4-808e207bed26%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Redefine%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20internet'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20core%20idea%20is%20simple%3A%20To%20use%20satellites%20to%20transmit%20some%20data%2C%20making%20the%20West%20less%20reliant%20on%20undersea%20cables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20ultimate%20ambition%20is%20to%20redefine%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20internet%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gregory%20Falco%2C%20an%20engineering%20professor%20at%20Cornell%20University%20working%20on%20HEIST.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20requiring%20all%20of%20our%20data%20to%20flow%20through%20subsea%20cables%20(of%20which%2095%25%20of%20the%20internet%20is%20reliant%20on)%20we%20would%20like%20to%20enable%20an%20ecosystem%20of%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20one%20may%20argue%20that%20submarine%20communication%20cables%20are%20very%20efficient%2C%20they%20are%20not%20very%20resilient%20to%20natural%20or%20human-made%20threats.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOverall%2C%20any%20measures%20to%20increase%20the%20resilience%20of%20our%20communications%20architecture%20is%20fundamentally%20needed.%20The%20multilayered%20approach%20of%20the%20HEIST%20program%20is%20a%20good%20start%2C%26quot%3B%20Melanie%20Garson%2C%20Associate%20Professor%20in%20Conflict%20Resolution%20%26amp%3B%20International%20Security%20at%20University%20College%20London%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e2c44d71-0342-4db7-b5da-d1d02750c87d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackup%20and%20deterrent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20works%20by%20fitting%20existing%20cables%20with%20sensors%20to%20detect%20disruptions%2C%20either%20from%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuspected-undersea-cable-sabotage-highlights-vulnerability-2024-12%23%3A~%3Atext%3DLast%2520month%252C%2520an%2520underwater%2520data%2Cthese%2520critical%2520undersea%2520lines%2520are.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20sabotage%20or%20natural%20events%20and%20accidents.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20outage%2C%20they%20would%20automatically%20re-route%20the%20data%20via%20a%20network%20of%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20act%20as%20a%20deterrent%2C%20giving%20hostile%20vessels%20less%20incentive%20to%20approach%20the%20cables%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFalco%20said%20the%20tech%20would%20be%20tested%20in%20January.%20From%20there%2C%20the%20plan%20is%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bend-to-end%20functional%20capability%26quot%3B%20by%20December%202026%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fiber%20optic%20cables%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c89e2643b5e59d16b4a008%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFiber%20optic%20cables%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%3Cp%3ESybille%20Reuter%20via%20Getty%20images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20already%20has%20its%20vast%20network%20of%20Starlink%20satellites%20beaming%20internet%20around%20the%20world%20to%20commercial%20customers%20and%20some%20militaries.%20But%20the%20service%20doesn't%20feature%20the%20rerouting%20concept%20HEIST%20is%20investigating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20SpaceX%20or%20Viasat%20responded%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cd177828-e44e-4bc8-851d-44513560e9e8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20threat%20to%20the%20cables%20is%20intensifying%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20Russia%20poses%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20cables%2C%20and%20has%20a%20motive%20to%20damage%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20analysts%20say%2C%20could%20seek%20to%20punish%20the%20West%20for%20its%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20by%20targeting%20crucial%20infrastructure%20like%20the%20cables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-secret-sub-unit-menaces-undersea-cables-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%20in%20August%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20a%20secret%20Russian%20undersea%20sabotage%20unit%2C%20the%20GUGI%2C%20had%20been%20surveilling%20the%20cables%2C%20which%20analysts%20warned%20that%20the%20West%20is%20ill-equipped%20to%20defend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d8ef0ca-e9d7-4528-9a99-adb2f875eec8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpace%20is%20dangerous%2C%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20having%20two%20methods%20is%20better%20than%20one%2C%20satellites%20are%20hardly%20immune%20from%20disruption%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpace%20weather%20events%20and%20collisions%20with%20debris%20(including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-nasa-need-better-space-debris-models-reduce-impact-risk-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanmade%20%26quot%3Bspace%20junk%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E)%20can%20damage%20satellites%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20attacks%20by%20rival%20powers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-could-attack-us-satellites-from-moon-warns-general-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20China%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20would%20likely%20target%20satellites%20if%20direct%20fighting%20were%20ever%20to%20break%20out%20between%20it%20and%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-nuclear-space-weapon-e